properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 3 at 1:25PM AKST until January 4 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of 3 to 5 inches.
Winds gusting as high as 30 mph in southern coastal locations.

* WHERE...Dixon Entrance to Cape Decision Coastal Area.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM AKST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow will be heavy with a high water
content.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM AKST SATURDAY FOR THE SOUTHERN OUTER COAST
